From: aorus-5090-egpu <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] AORUS Patch 0030 — UVM close-path DIAG instrumentation

Companion to Patch 0029 — extends close-path observability into the
UVM module so we can answer 'is the architecture.md Problem 4 close-
path bug class still load-bearing on the current driver stack?' with
empirical evidence, the same way Patch 0029 + tools/close-path-probe.sh
answered the /dev/nvidia0-side question.

PART A — pdev-based DIAG dump in nvidia.ko:

  tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump_pdev(struct pci_dev *, const char *site)
  EXPORT_SYMBOL'd. Same state capture as tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump
  (PMC_BOOT_0 + WPR2 + LnkSta + AER on GPU + bridge) but takes a
  pdev directly instead of nv_linux_state_t. Output uses [UVM-DIAG]
  tag to distinguish from the /dev/nvidia0-side [DIAG] events.
  Reads BAR0 from pci_resource_start(pdev, 0); the kernel's PCI
  resource table is authoritative here.

PART B — UVM-side instrumentation in nvidia-uvm.ko (uvm.c):

  Global atomic_t aorus_uvm_fd_count tracks /dev/nvidia-uvm fd count.
  Helper aorus_uvm_close_path_diag(site, fd_count, is_last_close)
  emits a one-line [CLOSE] marker; on LAST-CLOSE, additionally calls
  tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump_pdev + tb_egpu_dump_aer_trigger_event for
  full state + AER capture.

  GPU pdev lookup: pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot(0, 0x04, PCI_DEVFN(0,0)).
  Hardcoded to project topology (only NVIDIA device on this host).
  pci_dev_put after each use.

  Sites:
    - uvm-open-entry      — at end of uvm_open after success;
                            pre-increment count==0 ⇒ first-after-LAST-CLOSE
    - uvm-release-entry   — at top of uvm_release before any teardown
    - uvm-pre-destroy     — VA_SPACE branch only, just before
                            uvm_va_space_destroy (the actual
                            destabilising teardown)
    - uvm-post-destroy    — VA_SPACE branch only, just after
                            uvm_va_space_destroy
    - uvm-release-exit    — at end of uvm_release; post-decrement
                            count==0 ⇒ canonical LAST-CLOSE

  fd count tracking is at uvm_open success path (only count opens
  that returned NV_OK — kernel only calls release for those) and at
  uvm_release exit path (kernel guarantees release matches a prior
  successful open). Mismatched counts impossible by construction.

PART C — version.mk bump to aorus.12 to mark this build distinct
  from aorus.11 (Patch 0029 close-path DIAG).

Risk per feedback_observability_perturbs_bug: same passive
instrumentation pattern as Patch 0029 (ioremap+ioread32+iounmap +
PCI config-space reads only). pdev lookup adds one
pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot call per LAST-CLOSE site, which is a
kernel-internal lookup; no MMIO. Patch 0029 passive pattern verified
non-perturbing 2026-05-08; same expected here.

Refs: docs/architecture.md Problem 4; H22 ledger entry
      (close-path bug class mitigated /dev/nvidia0-side n=3);
      memory/project_close_path_mitigated_2026_05_08.md.
